					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85113223" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of smal halakhic works and extracts, by various authors.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85113223">
							<locus from="1r" to="63v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Collection</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">קובץ </title>
							<note>
								<p>The titles given on folio 2r include 8 pieces: responsa of Jacob of Marvege (she'elot halom) begins on folio 4r, responsa of Solomon ibn Adret begin on folio 16r, a letter of Abraham ben Moses ben Maimon begins on folio 26r, decisions of Gershom ben Judah Me᾿or ha-Golah and Judah he-Ḥasid, Seder hag῾alah begins on folio 31r , Seder niḳur le-Rashi begins on folio 33r, Sefer Mordekhai begins on folio 36r, and additional responsa (from folio 48r on). There are also additional halakhic fragments between the enlisted pieces.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>63 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>206</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>180/150</height>
										<width>120/85</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>63 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="28 33" writtenLines="28 33">
									<p>Non-uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Hard-point ruling is visible.</p>
									<p>Blank pages are left between the parts.</p>
									<p>Many marginal notes and additions are present.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="5">
							<summary>Italian cursive scripts of the latter part of the 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1 is a vellum flyleaf with a fragment of Rashi's commentary on Shemini.</p>
							<p>Folio 63 is a part of an Italian maḥzor or siddur of the 15th century.</p>
							<p>The titles on the title page (folio 2r) has been added in approximately 17th century.</p>
							<p>Mosheh Ḥizkiyah ha-Leṿi: inscribed, folio 61v.</p>
						</additions>
